cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DM, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with ordered point sets and their order types, which are fundamental concepts in computational geometry. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also discusses the complexity of recognizing instances of order type realizability, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of the existential theory of the reals and smoothed analysis suggests that it could also belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
